[1mFlags:[0m
      [36m--watch[0m                         Automatically restart the process on file change
      [36m--hot[0m                           Enable auto reload in the Bun runtime, test runner, or bundler
      [36m--no-clear-screen[0m               Disable clearing the terminal screen on reload when --hot or --watch is enabled
      [36m--smol[0m                          Use less memory, but run garbage collection more often
  [36m-r[0m, [36m--preload[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m                 Import a module before other modules are loaded
      [36m--require[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m                 Alias of --preload, for Node.js compatibility
      [36m--import[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m                  Alias of --preload, for Node.js compatibility
      [36m--inspect[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m                 Activate Bun's debugger
      [36m--inspect-wait[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m            Activate Bun's debugger, wait for a connection before executing
      [36m--inspect-brk[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m             Activate Bun's debugger, set breakpoint on first line of code and wait
      [36m--if-present[0m                    Exit without an error if the entrypoint does not exist
      [36m--no-install[0m                    Disable auto install in the Bun runtime
      [36m--install[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m                 Configure auto-install behavior. One of "auto" (default, auto-installs when no node_modules), "fallback" (missing packages only), "force" (always).
  [36m-i[0m                                  Auto-install dependencies during execution. Equivalent to --install=fallback.
  [36m-e[0m, [36m--eval[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m                    Evaluate argument as a script
  [36m-p[0m, [36m--print[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m                   Evaluate argument as a script and print the result
      [36m--prefer-offline[0m                Skip staleness checks for packages in the Bun runtime and resolve from disk
      [36m--prefer-latest[0m                 Use the latest matching versions of packages in the Bun runtime, always checking npm
      [36m--port[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m                    Set the default port for Bun.serve
      [36m--conditions[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m              Pass custom conditions to resolve
      [36m--fetch-preconnect[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m        Preconnect to a URL while code is loading
      [36m--max-http-header-size[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m    Set the maximum size of HTTP headers in bytes. Default is 16KiB
      [36m--dns-result-order[0m[2m[36m=<val>[0m        Set the default order of DNS lookup results. Valid orders: verbatim (default), ipv4first, ipv6first
      [36m--expose-gc[0m                     Expose gc() on the global object. Has no effect on Bun.gc().
      [36m--no-deprecation[0m                Suppress all reporting of the custom deprecation.
      [36m--throw-deprecation[0m             Determine whether or not deprecation warnings result in errors.
